eglected Tropical Diseases |volume=10 |issue=1 |pmc=4725727|ref=harv |pmid=26809063 |doi=10.1371/journal.pntd.0004399}}\n* {{cite journal |last1=Kazmi |first1=JH |last2=Pandit |first2=K |title=Disease and dislocation: the impact of refugee movements on the geography of malaria in NWFP, Pakistan |year=2001 |pages=1043\u20131055 |journal=Social Science & Medicine |volume=52 |issue=7 |url=  |doi=10.1016/S0277-9536(01)00341-0|pmid=12406471 |ref=harv}}\n* {{cite journal |last=Khamis |first=V |title=Post-traumatic stress disorder among school age Palestinian children |date=2005 |pages=81\u201395 |journal=Child Abuse Negl |volume=29 |issue=1|ref=harv|pmid=15664427 |doi=10.1016/j.chiabu.2004.06.013 }}\n* {{cite journal |last=Kolaczinski |first=J. H. |title=Subsidized Sales of Insecticide-Treated Nets in Afghan Refugee Camps Demonstrate the Feasibility of a Transition from Humanitarian Aid Towards Sustainability |year=2004 |pages=15 |journal=Malaria Journal |doi=10.1186/1475-2875-3-15 |pmid=15191614 |pmc=434525 |volume=3 |ref=harv}}\n* {{cite book |last=Lamey |first=Andy |title=Frontier Justice |year=2011 |publisher=Anchor Canada |isbn=978-0-385-66255-0 |location=Canada|ref=harv}}\n* {{cite web |author=Learn |title=Raising the voice of the invisible Urban Refugees &#124; Raising the voice of the invisible |date= |url=http://urban-refugees.org/ |publisher=Urban Refugees |accessdate=2015-12-18|ref=harv}}\n* {{cite web |last=Mahmoud |first=Hala W |title=Shattered dreams of Sudanese refugees in Cairo |url=http://www.fmreview.org/sites/fmr/files/FMRdownloads/en/FMRpdfs/FMR27/50.pdf |work=Forced Migration Review (FMR) |accessdate=9 July 2016 |ref=harv}}\n* {{cite web |last=Markus |first=Francis |title=Tanzania grants citizenship to 162,000 Burundian refugees in historic decision |date=17 October 2014 |url=http://www.unhcr.org/5441246f6.html |publisher=UNHCR |accessdate=9 July 2016 |ref=harv}}\n* {{cite book |last=McCarthy |first=Justin |title=Death and Exile: The Ethnic Cleansing of Ottoman Muslims, 1821\u20131922 |year=1995 |url=https://books.google.com/books?id=1ZntAAAAMAAJ |publisher=Darwin Press |isbn=978-0-87850-094-9|ref=harv}}\n* {{cite journal |last1=Mertans |first1=P |last2=Hall |first2=L |title=Malaria on the move: human population movement and malaria transmission |year=2000 |pages=103\u20139 |journal=Emerging Infectious Diseases |volume=6 |issue=2 |pmc=2640853|ref=harv|pmid=10756143 |doi=10.3201/eid0602.000202}}\n* {{cite book |last=Naimark |first=Norman |title=The Russians in Germany |year=1995 |publisher=Harvard University Press |ref=harv}}\n* {{cite news |title=Nairobi to open mission in Mogadishu |date=19 February 2014 |url=http://www.standardmedia.co.ke/mobile/?articleID=2000105058&story_title=nairobi-to-open-mission-in-mogadishu |accessdate=18 June 2016 |newspaper=Standard Digital|ref=CITEREFNairobi to open2014}}\n* {{cite web |title=Nansen International Office for Refugee: The Nobel Peace Prize 1938 |url=http://nobelprize.org/nobel_prizes/peace/laureates/1938/nansen-history.html |publisher=The Nobel Foundation|ref=CITEREFNansen International Office}}\n* {{cite web |title=The Nazi Ostarbeiter (Eastern Worker) Program |url=http://www.collectinghistory.net/ostarbeiter/index.html |website=Collectinghistory.net |ref=CITEREFNazi Ostarbeiter (Eastern}}\n* {{cite web |title=The Nobel Peace Prize 1938: Nansen International Office for Refugees |url=http://nobelprize.org/nobel_prizes/peace/laureates/1938/nansen-history.html |website=Nobelprize.org|ref=CITEREFNobel Peace Prize}}\n* {{cite web |author=Office of the United Nations High Commissioner for Refugees (UNHCR) |title=UNHCR Resettlement Handbook |date=July 2011 |page=19 |url=http://www.unhcr.org/46f7c0ee2.pdf |ref=harv}}\n* {{cite web |title=Old fears over new faces |date=21 September 2006 |url=http://seattletimes.nwsource.com/html/nationworld/2003265600_impghistory20.html |website=The Seattle Times |ref=CITEREFOld fears over2006}}\n* {{cite news |title=Patriots ignore greatest 